1 A BILL for an Act to create a committee to study special education funding during the 2025-26
2 interim; and to provide for a legislative management report.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. SPECIAL EDUCATION FUNDING COMMITTEE - REPORT TO
5 LEGISLATIVE MANAGEMENT.
6 1. During the 2025-26 interim, the legislative management shall establish and provide
7 staffing and administrative services to a committee to study special education funding.
8 The chairman of legislative management may add temporary, nonvoting members to
9 the committee, as deemed necessary by the committee, to serve without
10 compensation.
11 2. The committee may include:
12 a. Five members of the legislative assembly, appointed by the legislative
13 management;
14 b. Two multi-unit special education directors;
15 c. One large school special education director;
16 d. One special education coordinator;
17 e. One superintendent of a large school;
18 f. One superintendent of a small or midsize school;
19 g. One business manager of a large school; and
20 h. One multi-unit special education business manager.
21 3. During the 2025-26 interim, the special education funding committee study must
22 include a comprehensive review of special education funding models, including
23 student contracts, high-cost students, residential placement, and reimbursement under
24 the Medicaid program.
